\begin_layout Definition
The expectation, 
\begin_inset Formula $E\left[X\right]$
\end_inset

, of a random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is defined by 
\begin_inset Formula \[
E\left[X\right]=\begin{cases}
\sum_{i}x_{i}p(x_{i}), & \mbox{if }X\mbox{ is discrete,}\\
\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}xf(x)dx, & \mbox{if }X\mbox{ is continuous,}\end{cases}\]

\end_inset

 provided the relevant sum or integral is absolutely convergent, i.e.
 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{i}\mid x_{i}\mid p(x_{i})<\infty$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\mid x\mid f(x)dx<\infty$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Example
Assume 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is Binomial di stributed with 
\begin_inset Formula $n=5$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p=0.5$
\end_inset

.
 Then
\begin_inset Formula \begin{multline*}
E\left[X\right]=\sum_{i}x_{i}p(x_{i})=0\cdot\frac{1}{32}+1\cdot\frac{5}{32}+2\cdot\frac{10}{32}+3\cdot\frac{10}{32}+4\cdot\frac{5}{32}+5\cdot\frac{1}{32}=2.5\end{multline*}

\end_inset

The expected value need not correspond to a possible value of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

! 
